    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Horizontal, rectangular framed panels in Mesoamerican architecture, having their recessed surfaces often decorated with paintings or sculpture and the whole often cantilevered over sloping apron walls to form talud-tableros.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor horizontale, rechthoekige, omlijste panelen in de architectuur van Midden-Amerika, waarvan het inspringende oppervlak vaak is versierd met schilderingen of beeldhouwwerk, en waarbij het geheel vaak als een cantilever uitsteekt over hellende muren om talud-tableros te vormen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>中美洲式建築所採用的水平矩形框板，嵌壁板表面常有繪畫或雕刻，整組壁板常以懸臂方式搭建於傾斜的前護牆上方，進而構成神廟建築形式(talud-tablero)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
